# SLATE360 — Master System Contract
# Authoritative layout-layer rules for all Cursor chat sessions.
# Scope: UI, client components, data-client files, and layout refactors.
# Backend-only API/migration work is exempt from UI rules unless it renders UI.

---

## 0. Session Mandate

Slate360 is a production SaaS platform preparing for iOS and Android app-store submission.
Site Walk is the only fully visible authenticated app for Phase 1 release.

Before any UI work:
- Read `AGENTS.md` and `SLATE360_LIVE_MAIN_WORKFLOW.md`.
- Do not modify or create application router pages unless the task explicitly requests route work.
- Prefer canonical import roots: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks` — never `@/src` for new UI code.
- Never import from `_archived_context/`, `_v0_drop/`, or deleted legacy trees.

---

## 1. THE SIZED CODE CAP CONTRACT

Every single UI or data-client file created or refactored MUST remain strictly under **300 lines of code** (non-blank lines count toward readability; total file length must not exceed 300).

### Enforcement
- Hard ceiling: **300 lines per `.ts` / `.tsx` file** in `app/`, `components/`, and client-facing `lib/`.
- When a file approaches 250 lines, split immediately into focused submodules.
- Split by responsibility: hooks, types, presentational leaf components, orchestrators.
- Run `npm run guard:file-size-regression` before marking UI work complete.
- Existing baseline violations in `ops/file-size-baseline.json` may only grow with explicit owner approval; new files must never exceed 300 lines.

### Anti-patterns (forbidden)
- Monolithic page files mixing fetch, state, layout, and markup.
- God components with nested render functions spanning hundreds of lines.
- Copy-paste duplication instead of extraction into ≤300-line modules.

---

## 2. THE GEOMETRIC SHARP BOUNDARY

Rounded pill templates are programmatically **forbidden**.

### Required geometry
- All buttons, glass card panels, input boxes, select triggers, sheets, dialogs, and interactive targets MUST use a sleek structural rectangle with corner radius **exactly 12px**.
- Tailwind class: **`rounded-xl`** (12px at default scale).
- Allowed exceptions: fully circular avatars, status dots, map pins, and progress indicators where a circle is semantically required — NOT primary action buttons or card containers.

### Forbidden classes on interactive surfaces
- `rounded-full` on buttons, cards, inputs, modals, nav pills, or CTA chips.
- `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-3xl`, `rounded-[9999px]`, or arbitrary pill radii on the above surfaces.

### shadcn/ui alignment
- Override default shadcn radii in component variants to `rounded-xl` where they render buttons, cards, or inputs.
- Base token: `--radius: 0.75rem` (12px) when touching global theme variables.

---

## 3. THE GRAPHITE MATRIX BRAND BALANCING TOKENS

All new and refactored UI MUST consume these canonical color parameters.
Do not introduce ad-hoc hex values outside this palette without explicit owner approval.

| Token | Role | Hex |
|-------|------|-----|
| Root Canvas Background | Page / shell base | `#0B0F15` |
| Primary Interactive Asset Highlight | CTAs, active states, key accents | `#00E699` |
| High-Contrast Text Layer 1 | Headers, titles | `#FFFFFF` |
| High-Contrast Text Layer 2 | Body copy, descriptions | `#F8FAFC` |
| Secondary Structural Muted Tone | Labels, metadata, dividers | `#A3AED0` |

### CSS variable mapping (preferred)
```css
--graphite-canvas: #0B0F15;
--graphite-primary: #00E699;
--graphite-text-header: #FFFFFF;
--graphite-text-body: #F8FAFC;
--graphite-muted: #A3AED0;
```

### Tailwind usage guidance
- Backgrounds: `bg-[#0B0F15]` or registered theme token equivalent.
- Primary actions: `bg-[#00E699]` with dark readable foreground on teal (`#0B0F15`).
- Headers: `text-[#FFFFFF]`; body: `text-[#F8FAFC]`; muted: `text-[#A3AED0]`.
- Glass panels: dark graphite base with subtle border `border-white/10` or `border-[#A3AED0]/20`.

### Legacy palette note
Prior amber/cobalt tokens in `app/globals.css` are deprecated for new layout work.
Migrate touched surfaces to Graphite Matrix tokens; do not blend old amber CTAs with new teal primary in the same view.

---

## 4. THE AUTHORITATIVE VALUE-DRIVEN MICRO-COPY BLOCK

Automatic, generic AI website filler text is **strictly prohibited**.
All user-facing marketing, hero, product-definition, and pricing copy MUST be pulled exclusively from this dictionary template. Paraphrase only when grammar requires it; do not invent alternate value props, fake metrics, or placeholder lorem ipsum.

### Hero Header String
```
SLATE360 // REALITY INTELLIGENCE
```

### Core Descriptive Text
```
Precision reality capture for construction workflows. Capture site conditions instantly with Site Walk; inspect structural environments with interactive Digital Twins.
```

### Site Walk Definition Row
```
Single-handed field tracking, predictive tag chips classification, and instant document deliverable field report compilation.
```

### Pricing Card Option 1
```
Site Walk Pro Seat // $108 per month billed annually. Includes mobile camera capture, automated vector markups, blueprint pin drop maps, and synchronous PDF deliverable log outputs.
```

### Pricing Card Option 2
```
Enterprise Twin Suite // Custom volume pricing. Unlocks advanced 3D photogrammetry processing channels, tripod LiDAR point-cloud rendering spaces, and unlimited organizational collaborator seats.
```

### Copy discipline
- No "Coming Soon", "Beta", "Demo", "Lorem ipsum", or fake social proof inside authenticated app surfaces.
- No fabricated user counts, star ratings, or testimonial quotes unless sourced from real data.
- Site Walk remains the lead product in all public copy.

