## 5. Import & Layout Architecture Contract

### Canonical component roots (use these)
| Domain | Path |
|--------|------|
| shadcn/ui primitives | `@/components/ui/*` |
| Authenticated desktop shell | `@/components/dashboard/AppShell` |
| Authenticated chrome wrapper | `@/components/dashboard/AuthedAppShell` |
| Mobile command center | `@/components/walled-garden-dashboard` via `/app` |
| Site Walk V1 mobile shell | `@/components/site-walk/v1/*` |
| Capture V2 task flow | `@/components/capture-v2/*` |
| Mobile system tokens | `@/components/mobile-system/*` |
| Marketing homepage | `@/components/marketing-homepage` |

### Orphan / do-not-wire-without-migration
- `components/home/LandingPage.tsx` — superseded by `marketing-homepage.tsx`; do not attach to routes.
- `components/dashboard/DesignStudioShell.tsx` — duplicate; route uses `@/components/design-studio/DesignStudioShell`.
- `@/src/lib/*` — legacy split; migrate to `@/lib/*` when touched.

### Preview routes
Files under `app/preview/` and `app/(dashboard)/preview/` are sandbox only.
Do not import preview-only components into production route trees.

---

## 6. Stack & Primitive Requirements

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 App Router (`app/`), React 19.
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 + `app/globals.css` theme tokens.
- **Components**: shadcn/ui (New York style) via `@/components/ui/*`.
- **Radix**: Use unified `radix-ui` package imports (e.g. `Dialog as DialogPrimitive` from `radix-ui`).
- **Utilities**: `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`, CVA for variants, Lucide icons.

When adding shadcn components: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` then apply Graphite Matrix tokens and `rounded-xl` geometry.

---

## 7. Validation Before Completion

For any UI or layout-layer change:
1. `npm run typecheck`
2. `npm run build`
3. `npm run guard:architecture`
4. `npm run guard:file-size-regression` (when UI files touched)

Do not hide failures. Do not fix unrelated failures without explicit approval.

---

## 8. Git & Scope Discipline

- Do not use `git add .`
- Keep diffs narrow and reviewable
- Only commit when explicitly requested
- Default branch: `main` (see AGENTS.md for live-main workflow)

---

## 9. PASS A — ATOMIC FRONTEND LAYOUT REALIGNMENT

These three constraints are **absolute** for all layout-layer UI work. They override conflicting legacy patterns in touched files.

### 9.1 Logo Geometric Constants

The inline SVG asset inside `components/studio-ui/LogoProvider.tsx` is **prohibited** from using inherited font sizes or fluid parameters (`h-[1em]`, `em`-relative sizing, or parent font-size coupling).

| Viewport | Symbol (SVG) | Wordmark |
|----------|--------------|----------|
| Desktop (≥ 1024px) | `h-8 w-auto block shrink-0 text-[#00E699]` | `text-2xl font-bold tracking-[0.15em] text-white ml-4` |
| Mobile (< 1024px) | `h-6 w-auto block shrink-0 text-[#00E699]` | `text-lg font-bold tracking-[0.12em] text-white ml-2` |

- Logo wrapper MUST use `inline-flex items-center shrink-0` — no nested padding rows may compress the asset footprint.
- Pull `<Slate360Logo />` out of nested padding containers in header chrome.

### 9.2 Responsive Compilation Breakpoint Fork

| Viewport | Scroll container | Section tracks |
|----------|------------------|----------------|
| Desktop (≥ 1024px) | `h-[100dvh] snap-y snap-mandatory overflow-y-scroll scroll-smooth` | `h-[100dvh] snap-start relative overflow-hidden` |
| Mobile (< 1024px) | `h-auto` — **no** fixed viewport clips or snap parameters | `h-auto` fluid scrolling tracks with generous vertical padding (`py-16` minimum) to prevent overlapping text |

Mobile smartphone viewports are **strictly forbidden** from using `h-[100dvh]`, `snap-*`, or viewport-height clipping on section tracks.

### 9.3 Anti-Cartoon Design System

The following are **completely banned** on marketing and authenticated layout surfaces:
- Background card outlines around feature list items
- Emoji bullet nodes in feature copy (dropdown nav labels exempt)
- Text pill frames around feature points
- Early-2000s clip-art icons as list markers
- Checkmark (`✓`) nodes in feature columns

Feature points MUST render as flat, clean text columns using laser chevron nodes (`»`) in high-contrast Cybernetic Krypton Teal (`text-[#00E699]`).

### 9.4 Header & Product Dropdown Contract

Marketing header bar:
```
w-full h-16 fixed top-0 z-50 bg-[#0B0F15]/90 backdrop-blur-xl border-b border-white/[0.05] px-6 lg:px-12 flex justify-between items-center
```

Product dropdown MUST use React state (`isOpen`, `setIsOpen`) with click/focus listeners — **never** CSS-only `:hover` reveal (latency-plagued, collapses before click).

Dropdown panel (absolute below trigger):
```
absolute top-full right-0 mt-2 w-64 bg-[#0B0F15]/95 backdrop-blur-2xl border border-white/[0.08] rounded-xl p-2 shadow-2xl z-50
```

Dropdown row interaction:
```
text-slate-300 hover:text-[#00E699] hover:bg-white/[0.03] p-3 rounded-lg block text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-150
```

Clicking a row MUST smooth-scroll to its matching section ID and close the menu instantly.

